{{Infobox Artwork | image_file= El sueño de Jacob, por José de Ribera.jpg | image_size=360px | title=Jacob’s Dream | artist=[[Jusepe de Ribera|Lo Spagnoletto]] | year=1639 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=179 | width_metric=233 | height_imperial=70 | width_imperial=92 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Madrid]] | museum=[[Museo del Prado]] |other_language_1=Spanish|other_title_1=El sueño de Jacob}}
'''''Jacob’s Dream''''' ({{lang-es|'''El sueño de Jacob'''}}) is a 1639 oil-on-canvas painting by the Spanish [[Tenebrist]] painter [[José de Ribera]] (''Lo Spagnoletto'').
== Description == It measures {{convert|179|x|233|cm|in}} and is in the [[Museo del Prado]] in Madrid.
== Analysis == [[Jacob]] appears as a shepherd sleeping, resting on his left shoulder with a tree behind him. In the background on the other side is [[Jacob's Ladder|the ladder]] that he sees in his dream. It is not a wooden ladder but a ladder of light, by which [[angel]]s are ascending and descending.
==References== *[https://www.museodelprado.es/visita-el-museo/15-obras-maestras/ficha-obra/zoom/2/obra/el-sueno-de-jacob/oimg/0/ El sueño de Jacob], El Prado *[http://libmma.contentdm.oclc.org/cdm/ref/collection/p15324coll10/id/81943 ''Jusepe de Ribera, 1591-1652 ''], Issued in connection with an exhibition held Sept. 18-Nov. 29, 1992, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York (see pages: 135-137).
{{Jusepe de Ribera}}
